    "For the orientation dataset, the model performs an 8-class classification to detect an arrow's direction for evaluating its basic spatial reasoning.",
    "In assessing LVLM robustness, we consider performance consistency, which measures whether a model maintains its task-specific metrics across visual variations, by quantifying how these variations impact model performance:",
    "where M (I v) denotes the task-specific metric on variation I v, M represents the mean performance across all variations, and V is the set of variations.",
    "A larger C m indicates better consistency, with 1 representing that the model is robust enough to be unaffected by visual variations.",
    "We also evaluate the output stability of model generation, at both semantic and token levels:"
  ],
